Verify Setting Single Error Log As Resolved
[Documentation] Select and mark a single error log as resolved through GUI and verify via Redfish.
Instead of sleep use wait condition for successful message to appear.
Kindly include a verification step to ensure that the error log has been marked as resolved in the Redfish API.
Remove these and use "List Should Not Contain Value" to verify the list.
Verify Resolving A Single Error Log In GUI
Why is this login required again? A Login is already done at the suite level.
In the before testcase[Verify Displayed Event Details With Redfish]  -->>Redfish.Logout is there so Redfish.Login required here
Can you please fix the suite to eliminate login at test case level? Login and logout should be at suite level only. I am fine if you want to do it in a separate commit.
Create a keyword that gets the event state and verifies whether it is True or False.
Verify Resolving Multiple Error Logs In GUI
Select and mark multiple error logs as resolved through GUI

New keyword pls as said above.

Rename the variable name to error_logs_status

1. You can use this for both single and multiple error logs. So remove the method 
Get Single Event Log Redfish Status
2. Rename to 'Get Event Logs Status From Redfish'

Don't use data type in variable names --> list
The variable name should be resolved_status or events_status..
Please avoid using class, @name, title and arial in xpath name. If you are find data-test-id let me know, let me know.

```
GUI:Added tests to verify resolved error logs

Changes:
    -Below test cases are added with this commit
       Verify Resolving Single Error Log In GUI
       Verify Resolving Multiple Error Logs In GUI
```
[Documentation]  Verify that error logs can be resolved via GUI and the resolution is reflected in Redfish.
Not required to check error log resolved because every new error log will come as unresolved
Here you are selecting all events instead on one single. Please correct this.
Instead on this, I would say wait until notification gets disappear
Above comment are applicable for this test case also.
Get And Verify Value Of Resolved Attribute For Event Logs

This keyword needs to take action based on error log provided. Like take error log id as the argument and then check if those are marked as resolved

or directly do this verification in the above test cases.
